Sentencas: La1-xSrxFe0.7Ni0.3O3-delta (x = 0, 0.1 and 0.2, LSFNx) are investigated as both cathode and anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: La1-xSrxFe0.7Ni0.3O3-δ as both cathode and anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The structure, microstructure and electrochemical properties of these materials are studied under oxidizing and reducing atmospheres.
Titulo: La1-xSrxFe0.7Ni0.3O3-δ as both cathode and anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In air, the electrodes exhibit polarization resistance of 0.1 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C under open circuit voltage.
Titulo: La1-xSrxFe0.7Ni0.3O3-δ as both cathode and anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In a H-2 atmosphere, Ni nanoparticles are exsolved on the surface, leading to a polarization resistance as low as 0.06 Omega cm(2) .
Titulo: La1-xSrxFe0.7Ni0.3O3-δ as both cathode and anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A cell with a 350 mu m thick La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta electrolyte and LSFN electrodes generates a power output of 540 mWcm(-2)
Titulo: La1-xSrxFe0.7Ni0.3O3-δ as both cathode and anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: at 800 degrees C. Moreover, stable values of power density are obtained after successive oxidation/reduction cycles, confirming the reversibility of the electrodes.
Titulo: La1-xSrxFe0.7Ni0.3O3-δ as both cathode and anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
